<li id="cite_note-ellul-41"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-ellul_41-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ellul_41-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFEllul1988" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Jacques_Ellul" title="Jacques Ellul">Ellul, Jacques</a> (1988). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=55_Oa12YTt0C&amp;q=Anarchy%20and%20Christianity&amp;pg=PA86"><i>Anarchy and Christianity</i></a>. Michigan: Wm. B. Eerdmans. pp.&#160;86–87. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780802804952" title="Special:BookSources/9780802804952"><bdi>9780802804952</bdi></a>. <q>The Interpretation of Romans 13:1-2</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Anarchy+and+Christianity&amp;rft.place=Michigan&amp;rft.pages=86-87&amp;rft.pub=Wm.+B.+Eerdmans&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.isbn=9780802804952&amp;rft.aulast=Ellul&amp;rft.aufirst=Jacques&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D55_Oa12YTt0C%26q%3DAnarchy%2520and%2520Christianity%26pg%3DPA86&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristianity+and+politics" class="Z3988"></span></span>
